From Ed Haymore Subject Re modems and noisy lines Chris Crayton wrote JCL this garbage , my modem doesn't have any of these on hardware, can a JCL software implemented protocol do the trick There is a software version of MNP available from MTEZ, and it will often connect with other modems that are MNP compatible, but if the modem that you There's also a program called ODYSSEY MODEM directory on the Simtel archives that emulates MNP and others, too, I think, but these were what I was interested in I was getting a lot of garbage when I called one number, and MNP cleared it up completely on my ordinary modem Fortunately, the remote end had an MNP modem I tried MNP , too, but it seemed to lock up the computer Your mileage may vary Ed Haymore